[SN]TITLE[SN]
Denton 'drug driver' crash leaves girl, 10, injured

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A girl was seriously hurt in a crash involving a suspected drug driver.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 10-year-old was struck as she crossed the road on Friday and suffered a fractured skull, broken legs and pelvis and a bleed to the brain.
A man, 26, was detained on suspicion of drug driving and dangerous driving causing serious injury, after the crash at about 20:00 BST.
A van driver who is a potential witness to the crash, in Manchester Road, Denton, is urged to contact police.
